-- Fiji Beats Wales 26-19 to Win Hong Kong Sevens Rugby Title
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-03-24T11:48:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-24/fiji-beats-wales-26-19-to-win-hong-kong-sevens-rugby-title.html
Fiji rallied to beat Wales 26-19
and defend its Hong Kong Sevens rugby title.  Osea Kolinisau scored three second-half tries as the
Fijians, who trailed 19-0 at halftime of the Cup final, fought
back to claim their second tournament victory in the
International Rugby Board’s 2012-2013 Sevens World Series.  New Zealand  tops the standings with  113 points  through six
of nine events. Fiji’s victory lifted it to second place with 88
points.  The next tournament is scheduled March 30-31 in Tokyo.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  